	<h2>Commercial Fencing Materials: Comprehensive Comparison</h2>

	<h3>Chain Link Fencing (Commercial Grade)</h3>
	<p><strong>Why It's Popular for Stockton Businesses:</strong> Chain link offers the best value for large-scale perimeter security, making it ideal for warehouses, industrial yards, and storage facilities throughout Stockton's commercial districts.</p>

	<p><strong>Commercial-Grade Specifications:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Fabric Gauge:</strong> 9-gauge minimum (heavier than residential 11-gauge)</li>
		<li><strong>Height:</strong> 6-12 feet depending on security needs</li>
		<li><strong>Mesh Size:</strong> 2-inch standard, 1-inch for enhanced security</li>
		<li><strong>Framework:</strong> 2-3/8" or 2-7/8" line posts, 3-1/2" to 6" terminal posts</li>
		<li><strong>Top Treatment:</strong> Barbed wire or razor ribbon for high-security applications</li>
		<li><strong>Coating:</strong> Galvanized (standard) or vinyl-coated (enhanced durability/appearance)</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Cost Analysis:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>6-foot Galvanized:</strong> $8-15 per linear foot installed</li>
		<li><strong>8-foot Galvanized:</strong> $12-20 per linear foot installed</li>
		<li><strong>Vinyl-Coated (Color):</strong> Add $3-6 per linear foot</li>
		<li><strong>Barbed Wire Top:</strong> Add $2-4 per linear foot</li>
		<li><strong>Privacy Slats:</strong> Add $4-8 per linear foot</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Best Applications:</strong> Warehouses, industrial yards, equipment storage, utility facilities, construction sites, wholesale operations</p>

	<p><strong>Pros:</strong> Most economical for large perimeters, durable (20+ years), see-through provides visibility, widely available, easy repairs</p>

	<p><strong>Cons:</strong> Industrial appearance, no privacy without slats, can be climbed without deterrents, minimal aesthetic appeal</p>

